summary: Will that be all, Mr. Stark?
title: Will that be all, Mr. Stark?
body:
by IronSwordStarShield (SweetFanfics)

They feed each other most of the meal, Tony, for once, not arguing about how much he should eat because he doesn’t want to do anything to break this delicate mood between them. Conversation flows between them, touching on a multitude of topics but their voices never rise above a soft, private murmur. Tony feels like he’s trapped in a bubble, like his office is cut off from the rest of the world. The idea appeals to him, especially when Steve’s cheeks turn a fetching shade of pink when Tony deliberately licks Steve’s chopsticks after accepting the tamagoyaki.

–
Steve brings dinner to Tony in his office and things escalate, that’s it. That’s the whole story.

summary: I'm scared about this dark Tony Stark secret people are saying is in Far From Home. I really hope it won't tarnish Tony's...
body:
I’m scared about this dark Tony Stark secret people are saying is in Far From Home. I really hope it won’t tarnish Tony’s reputation as The Real Hero.

Anyway, there are a lot of theories out there like Tony is Peter’s biological father (highly unlikely) or that it was because of SI’s former weapon dev business that killed Peter’s parents or Ben or it was SI’s experimentations that resulted to a radioactive spider biting Peter…

There are others but I haven’t seen a theory about Arno Stark. Like, what if we get an MCU version of Arno but he’s a bad guy and HATES Tony.

Just putting that out there. It could be interesting.

by starkyoukai

Hello and welcome to the Vishanti Venture. This is a sequel to the story I wrote that is called No-One But You (Only The Good Die Young)

It specifically follows the Vishanti trio. Tony Stark, Dr. Stephen Strange, and Steve Rogers. If you haven’t read the first fic, haven’t reached the part in the story with the Vishanti, or if don’t know what that is in the Marvel Universe, please don’t fret.

I will provide you a fic that really doesn’t need the previous one. It will stand alone. There will be explained references, but I will provide context. The end of the first fic really leaves the three main characters in a world and a journey that is completely separate. I’m working on my fiction writing so feedback is always greatly appreciated.

This continuation or “sequel” takes place a year and six months after the last chapter.
